        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 8:17PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fowler, or 27 miles west of La Junta, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fowler, Manzanola, and Olney Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
